reviewText: The story of Saint Tail comes to an end in this boxset. For me, the ending was quite unexpected and exceeded my expectations. The little twists they threw in the story keep things interesting as the story reaches it's climax. If you've loved Saint Tail so far, you're going to love the ending. A fitting end to a sweet tale at a great price for the high number of episodes in this DVD set.Only negative part of this boxset was the incredible amount of filler episodes. I found myself skipping through some of the episodes because they didn't have anything important to contribute to the main storyline. Could have been a better show if it had less filler episodes but all in all a cute enjoyable show.
Title: Saint Tail: The Enchanted Collection - Volume 6

reviewText: A great ending to a great series. Nothing childish or silly about it. Wish they had finished it in English, but still highly enjoyable. If you liked KKJeanne, get this!
Title: Saint Tail: The Enchanted Collection - Volume 6

reviewText: This is so good..... But its only in japanese not dubbed in english.Theres eps 23-43 in the boxset. Contains the final 21episodes in the series..
Title: Saint Tail: The Enchanted Collection - Volume 6

reviewText: If you like Sailor Moon, Pretear, CCS, Kaleido Star,Wedding Peach,Tokyo Mew Mew, etc. give this a try. I don't think it reached as many people as it could have given that it was never finished in English dubbing. But just because it didn't get as much exposure doesn't make it any less as good as say Wedding Peach, Tokyo MM, or CCS.
Title: Saint Tail: The Enchanted Collection - Volume 6

reviewText: I love Saint Tail but I feel the Anime is lacking in many ways. Sure this volume is lacking an english track but it also lacks the charm of the manga. The music ages this series by thirty years. I heard this show was made in the mid 1990s but I thought I heard seventies music and the lack luster animation verifies this impression what is up with cheesy seventies music in Anime.The anime has its good points such as additional stories that you won't find in the manga. The character designs are much cleaner than the manga version. Additional screen time for the parents of the heroine.I can conclude with a final note that this is a nice treat for those who haven't read the manga enjoy.
Title: Saint Tail: The Enchanted Collection - Volume 6
